Sentencas: High-resolution transmission and scanning electron microscopy of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anodes made of Ni and yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ), revealed a substantial microstructural reconstruction induced by the anodic current.
Titulo: Ion transfer in Ni-containing composite anodes of solid oxide fuel cells: A microstructural study

Sentencas: These microstructural alterations, primarily the growth of NiO inclusions at the Ni vertical bar YSZ interface, the resultant orientation relationship between the NiO and YSZ grains, and Ni grain fragmentation on subsequent reduction, provide a straightforward evidence for the so-called oxygen spillover mechanism of the anodic reaction.
Titulo: Ion transfer in Ni-containing composite anodes of solid oxide fuel cells: A microstructural study
